<h3>The Performing and Visual Arts Scholarships Eureka College</h3>
<h4>Performance at Eureka</h4>
	<p>The Performing and Visual Arts Scholarships are designed to recognize   those students with outstanding talent in drama, music, or art. Grants/scholarships are awarded based on talent in those areas. </p>
	<p><a href="#art">Art Scholarships</a> |<a href="#piano"> Piano Scholarships</a> | <a href="#theatre">Theatre Scholarships</a> | <a href="#vocal">Vocal Scholarships</a> | <a href="#info">For more information</a></p>

<a id="art"></a>
<h5>Art Scholarships</h5>
	<p>All freshman Art majors, minors and double majors are eligible for a $1,000 annually renewable portfolio-based scholarship. A portfolio review, one  letter of reference from a former teacher and an artistâ€™s statement are required before the scholarship can be awarded. The statement should include  one page of career goals and a description of the art that is included in the portfolio. The portfolio review usually takes place either in the fall or  spring semester prior to the first week of classes in the fall semester of the freshman year.&nbsp;Transfer students beginning their first semester at Eureka College are also eligible for a portfolio scholarship award. </p>
	<p><a href="">Download all requirements and evaluation points &gt;</a></p>

<a id="piano"></a>
<h5>Applied Piano Scholarships</h5>
	<p>Annual awards in piano performance, in the amount of $1,000, are currently awarded to all incoming majors in Music. These awards are annually renewable based upon the following criteria which will be assessed at the end of each academic semester.</p>
	<p><a href="" target="_blank">Download all requirements and evaluation points &gt;</a></p>

<a id="theatre"></a>
<h5>Theatre Scholarships</h5>
	<p>To acquire the Fine &amp; Performing Arts Theatre Scholarship, please contact Holly Rocke, Professor of Theatre &amp; Drama. To obtain and continue this scholarship, students will be required to log a minimum of 15 hours of service per semester to the Theatre Department. Service hours can be earned by helping to build and paint sets, working on lights, sound, make-up, ticket sales, and many other opportunities. Please share details with <a href="mailto: hrocke@eureka.edu">Professor Rocke</a> about how the student has worked with any theatre &amp; drama in the past and/or how the student might like to help with theatre at Eureka College.</p>
	<p><a href="">Download a Recommendation Form &gt;</a></p>

<a id="vocal"></a>	
<h5>Vocal Music Scholarships</h5>
	<p>Annual vocal music awards, in the amount of $1,000, are currently granted  to all incoming majors in  Music. These awards are annually renewable based up on the following criteria which will be assessed at the end  of each academic semester.</p>
